 plenty of accessories, including a window cleaner, round scrubbing brushes, an angled nozzle, a jet nozzle, a scoop nozzle and a brass brush. A tool caddy attaches directly to the steamer mop and makes carrying all the attachments convenient, but the caddy doesn&#39;t hook very snugly to the steamer, so it is prone to falling off.","In our hands-on tests, this steamer was difficult to assemble. Snapping the head into place and getting the pad to stay put was frustrating, but it worked fine once we figured it out. Also, this steam cleaner has a small tank with a tiny fill spout that makes it tricky to fill up before cleaning. We used a thin measuring cup with a narrow pour spout that was just the right size. This was an accessory with another mop we tested, but since Gruene doesn’t include a similar accessory, you will have to be creative when figuring out the best way to fill up the tank. Given the size of the tank, if you have a relatively large space to clean, you’ll have to fill the tank up at least a couple times.","Steam is only emitted when you press the button on the steam mop, so you control when and where you want steam. However, this makes it difficult to clean objects that you need to hold in place while also maneuvering the machine and pressing the button. Another downside to this versatile steam mop is that it tends to leave some water behind after you steam a flat surface such as a glass tabletop or a laminate floor. One other concern is the cord length is only 20 feet. While this is long enough for many living spaces, it is one of the shortest cords of any of the mops in our lineup. If your home or living space is bigger than average you’ll be unplugging frequently and finding new outlets.","This floor steam cleaner comes with a one-year warranty, which is fairly standard. If you have questions or concerns while assembling or using the product, you can contact customer support via email or phone."]},"id":"f2260b30-9284-400c-b8fb-20b4350558b3","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Summary"},"id":"398a3d49-a8ed-41eb-9e46-99dfc269abec","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["The versatility of the Gruene Clean System makes it a good choice if you plan to clean more than just your floors. It can be repurposed to clean both hard floors and countertops. It comes with a variety of accessories that clean different surfaces and let you access hard-to-reach areas. The shorter-than-average cord length limits its coverage, but hopefully you’ll have plenty of outlets to facilitate cleaning all of your surface area. The small tank and corresponding tiny fill spout will make cleaning large spaces more work than it should be. If you&#39;re mainly focused on floors, you might need to consider whether the minor inconveniences are things you can live with."]},"id":"8bc60e7c-321c-46cc-91c8-c348ed684623","type":"text"}]],"body":null,"legacyId":"product_review_page_62070","url":"/gruene-review","authors":[{"email":"","slug":"angie-parkinson","url":"/author/angie-parkinson","dateCreated":"2019-04-16T16:01:12Z","name":"Angie Parkinson","dateModified":"2019-04-16T16:01:12Z","id":"4Pu3Dbh8P3CR8CNSJRVPZP","dateImported":null,"site":"toptenreviews"}],"territories":["US","GB"],"companies":[],"dateCreated":"2015-01-05T22:51:39Z","datePublished":"2015-01-05T22:51:39Z","name":"Gruene Clean System GR-2N1","synopsis":"Editor’s Note: This product has been removed from our side-by-side comparison because it has been discontinued.","review":{"rating":74,"verdict":"The Gruene Clean System is a versatile cleaning machine with a variety of accessories that let you clean hard floors and hard-to-reach countertop areas. This steam mop will work best for apartments and average-sized homes.","pros":["As both a steam mop and handheld steamer, this device will clean a variety of surfaces."],"cons":["It&#8217;s difficult to assemble and has a tiny fill spout."]},"strapline":"Editor’s Note: This product has been removed from our side-by-side comparison because it